(fn compare [lt x y]
    ;; With only two data points, we can't confirm that `lt` is
    ;; actually the strict order relation that we are assuming it to
    ;; be.  We can at least confirm irreflexivity and antisymmetry.
    {:pre [(not (lt x x)),
           (not (lt y y)),
           (not (and (lt x y) (lt y x)))]} 
    (cond 
      (lt x y)  :lt
      (lt y x)  :gt
      :else     :eq))
